**Full command executed:**

```bash
engram learn feedback \
  --position top \
  --chunk-source "sess-a.jsonl#turn-3" \
  --chunk-source "sess-b.jsonl#turn-7" \
  --source "Two parallel test failures (sessions a and b)" \
  --situation "Parallel Go table-driven tests" \
  --behavior "Sharing fixture map across parallel test subtests" \
  --impact "Causes flaky failures and race conditions" \
  --action "Each subtest must receive its own copy of the fixture map"
```

This crystallizes the non-obvious constraint (not just "use table tests", but "isolate mutable state in parallel tests") and links it to the evidence of the twice-repeated failure.
